        <div class="doc-box__breakout">
            <ul class="doc-box__breakout-meta">
                <li>
                    <span class="doc-box__breakout-meta-label">ADMITTED</span>
                    <span>03/08/2015</span>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="doc-box__breakout-meta-label">DISCHARGED</span>
                    <span>03/14/2015</span>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                I had a long discussion with the family and the patient and she
                really did not want to have any treatment. She developed severe
                respiratory distress, was kept comfortable, per her and her
                family's wishes, and she expired on 03/14/2015.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
            
    
<figcaption class="attribution">
    
    
    
    </figcaption>


</figure>

        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="202.0">Nadine’s parents asked St. Peter’s to investigate the care she received. They wanted to know how Weiner could have missed a massive tumor a week before she died. Two months later, they met with the hospital’s director of risk management, who told them, Long said, “that he was reviewed and provided great care.”</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="203.0">For nine years, that answer had satisfied them. Believing Weiner had spared Nadine of pain in death, they put up a “We Stand With Doctor Weiner” sign in their yard. But now, having looked at Nadine’s medical file, they wanted to know if they had been manipulated, if she was actually terminal. Citing confidentiality laws, St. Peter’s has refused to provide the family the review, nor would it confirm to me that a review exists.</p>
        
    
                    

<figure
    data-pp-id="204"
    data-pp-blocktype="image"
    class="bb-image size12 center  wide-sm wrap 
                ">

    


                    
    


    <img
        class=""
        alt=""
        width="3000"
        height="2001"
        loading="lazy" js-autosizes        src="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/20240716-Johns-MontanaDoctor-24_preview_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_embedColorProfile_true_quality_95.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fm=webp&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=534&amp;q=75&amp;w=800&amp;s=c92bb5730ebc0053607717b3aa4cdb97"
