        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/unitedhealth-healthcare-insurance-denial-ulcerative-colitis">
                                    Inside UnitedHealth’s Effort to Deny Coverage for a Patient’s Care
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            After a college student finally found a treatment that worked, the insurance giant decided it wouldn’t pay for the costly drugs. His fight to get coverage exposed the insurer’s hidden procedures for rejecting claims.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/david-armstrong">David Armstrong</a>, ProPublica; <span class="name">Patrick Rucker</span>, <a href="https://thecapitolforum.com/">The Capitol Forum</a>;  and <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/maya-miller">Maya Miller</a>, ProPublica,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2023-02-02EST05:00">Feb. 2, 2023, 5 a.m. EST</time>
        </p>

